revious attempts at peace talks for the southern provinces (2006 - 2014). I will also argue that the MARA initiative has been the last in a list of false starts at building a credible peace process for the south since the conflict began in 2004 and that developments in January 2020 should be interpreted as a turning point for the conflict.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 66047790, "asset_id": 42038694, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 11002720, "first_name": "Gerard", "last_name": "McDermott", "domain_name": "cityu-hk", "page_name": "GerMcDer", "display_name": "Gerard McDermott", "profile_url": "https://cityu-hk.academia.edu/GerMcDer?f_ri=1948480", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/11002720/3268019/77363197/s65_gerard.mcdermott.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 1198, "name": "Peace and Conflict Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Peace_and_Conflict_Studies?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 6818, "name": "Malaysia", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malaysia?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 10096, "name": "Thailand", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Thailand?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 12939, "name": "Armed Conflict", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Armed_Conflict?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 13614, "name": "Conflict Resolution", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Conflict_Resolution?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 15473, "name": "Muslims in Southern Thailand", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Muslims_in_Southern_Thailand?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 38972, "name": "ASEAN", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/ASEAN?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 46563, "name": "Conflict Mediation Strategies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Conflict_Mediation_Strategies?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 61735, "name": "Dr Mahathir Mohamad", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Dr_Mahathir_Mohamad?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 151172, "name": "Negotiations", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Negotiations?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 204791, "name": "NSC", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/NSC?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 271987, "name": "Kuala Lumpur", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Kuala_Lumpur?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 364561, "name": "Separatism", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Separatism?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 870628, "name": "Bnpp", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Bnpp?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 1300332, "name": "Mara", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Mara?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 1381439, "name": "PULO", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/PULO?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 1381440, "name": "BRN", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/BRN?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 1385389, "name": "2019", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/2019?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 1496948, "name": "General Prayuth", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/General_Prayuth?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 1948480, "name": "Pattani, Yala & Narathiwat", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Pattani_Yala_and_Narathiwat?f_ri=1948480"}]}, {"id": 44416191, "title": "Cross-Cultural Communication: Communication Accommodation Experiences of Pattani Students with Javanese Students at IAIN Tulungagung", "created_at": "2020-11-01T22:01:26.418-08:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/44416191/Cross_Cultural_Communication_Communication_Accommodation_Experiences_of_Pattani_Students_with_Javanese_Students_at_IAIN_Tulungagung?f_ri=1948480", "dom_id": "work_44416191", "summary": "Cultural differences between native and Indonesian culture makes foreign students in Indonesia experience a culture shock. Such case occurs on students from Pattani, South Thailand, who study in IAIN Tulungagung. To overcome that culture shock, Pattani students do communication accommodation to make them feel comfortable in a new environment, and thus can be accepted by Javanese students from Indonesia. This research was a kind of qualitative study. The data were collected by using observation and interview techniques. To find out the forms of communication accommodation performed by Pattani students, the researchers adopted communication accommodation theory by Giles. The results of this research revealed that there were two forms of communication accommodation performed by Pattani student. Firstly, convergence, was performed when Pattani students tried to level communication behavior with their speech partners. Convergence done by Pattani students can be classified into pre-convergence, convergence process, and post convergence. Secondly, divergence is defending Pattani identity when communicating with Javanese students. Divergence accommodation was performed in two forms namely verbal and non-verbal.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 64828694, "asset_id": 44416191, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 5833349, "first_name": "Dwi", "last_name": "Nurhayati", "domain_name": "iain-tulungagung", "page_name": "Dwiastuti", "display_name": "Dwi A S T U T I W A H Y U Nurhayati", "profile_url": "https://iain-tulungagung.academia.edu/Dwiastuti?f_ri=1948480", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/5833349/2505010/15147517/s65_nur.khairiah.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 2149, "name": "Indonesian Culture", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Indonesian_Culture?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 15874, "name": "Cultural differences in communications styles", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Cultural_differences_in_communications_styles?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 46675, "name": "Culture Shock", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Culture_Shock?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 138084, "name": "Verbal and Non Verbal Language", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Verbal_and_Non_Verbal_Language?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 317226, "name": "Communication Accomodation Theory", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Communication_Accomodation_Theory?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 1948480, "name": "Pattani, Yala & Narathiwat", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Pattani_Yala_and_Narathiwat?f_ri=1948480"}]}, {"id": 45594868, "title": "Review of 'Kingdom's Edge' by Jim Pollard", "created_at": "2021-03-22T07:21:21.565-07:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/45594868/Review_of_Kingdoms_Edge_by_Jim_Pollard?f_ri=1948480", "dom_id": "work_45594868", "summary": null, "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 66082180, "asset_id": 45594868, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 11002720, "first_name": "Gerard", "last_name": "McDermott", "domain_name": "cityu-hk", "page_name": "GerMcDer", "display_name": "Gerard McDermott", "profile_url": "https://cityu-hk.academia.edu/GerMcDer?f_ri=1948480", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/11002720/3268019/77363197/s65_gerard.mcdermott.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 38972, "name": "ASEAN", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/ASEAN?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 96933, "name": "Politics in Thailand", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Politics_in_Thailand?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 1948480, "name": "Pattani, Yala & Narathiwat", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Pattani_Yala_and_Narathiwat?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}]}, {"id": 26858257, "title": "Southeast Asia\u2019s Race-Based Conflicts vis-a-vis ASEAN Regional Integration", "created_at": "2016-07-09T10:53:49.683-07:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/26858257/Southeast_Asia_s_Race_Based_Conflicts_vis_a_vis_ASEAN_Regional_Integration?f_ri=1948480", "dom_id": "work_26858257", "summary": "The current presentation is an offshoot of an ongoing project of collaborators driven by the question of growing incidences of ethnic conflict within Southeast Asian countries--all of them members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN). The presentation makes three major arguments and observations. First, Southeast Asia\u2019s ethnic, political, and cultural diversity already poses a major hurdle towards a common community. Second, ASEAN\u2019s \u201cnon-interference\u201d clause allows each member state to respond to diversity with exclusionary and discriminatory nation-building, as a means of increasing legibility in governance. Third, a proposed model shows how each Southeast Asian country's nation-building policies favor a particular/existing ethnic or \u201cethno-religious\u201d majority, resemble racist ideology, causing domestic conflicts and stymies meaningful regional exchange. The study also points to further points of inquiry and research to address this phenomenon.\n", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 47128259, "asset_id": 26858257, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 403456, "first_name": "Hansley", "last_name": "Juliano", "domain_name": "ateneo", "page_name": "HansleyJuliano", "display_name": "Hansley  Juliano", "profile_url": "https://ateneo.academia.edu/HansleyJuliano?f_ri=1948480", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/403456/126465/8287958/s65_hansley.juliano.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 796, "name": "Comparative Politics", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Comparative_Politics?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 797, "name": "International Relations", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/International_Relations?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 1031, "name": "Southeast Asian Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Southeast_Asian_Studies?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 8787, "name": "Singapore", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Singapore?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 15466, "name": "Bangsamoro Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Bangsamoro_Studies?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 22559, "name": "Philippine Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Philippine_Studies?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 37322, "name": "Burmese/Myanmar history", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Burmese_Myanmar_history?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 46666, "name": "Human Rights in Asia / ASEAN", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Human_Rights_in_Asia_ASEAN?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 47767, "name": "Singapore Politics", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Singapore_Politics?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 96933, "name": "Politics in Thailand", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Politics_in_Thailand?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 131971, "name": "Global Politics", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Global_Politics?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 183140, "name": "ASEAN Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/ASEAN_Studies?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 552165, "name": "Rohingya Muslims", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Rohingya_Muslims?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 840729, "name": "The ASEAN Economic Community and New Regionalism", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/The_ASEAN_Economic_Community_and_New_Regionalism?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 1155653, "name": "Rohingyas", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Rohingyas?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 1383357, "name": "Pattani", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Pattani?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 1948480, "name": "Pattani, Yala & Narathiwat", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Pattani_Yala_and_Narathiwat?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 2493247, "name": "Racism in Asia", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Racism_in_Asia?f_ri=1948480"}, {"id": 2493248, "name": "Racism in Singapore", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Racism_in_Singapore?f_ri=1948480"}]}, {"id": 35472959, "title": "New Trends in Southeast Asia's Ethno-Nationalist Conflicts Post-Regional Integration", "created_at": "2017-12-19T21:51:45.895-08:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/35472959/New_Trends_in_Southeast_Asias_Ethno_Nationalist_Conflicts_Post_Regional_Integration?f_ri=1948480", "dom_id": "work_35472959", "summary": "This work is an ongoing project of collaborators driven by the question of persisting incidences of ethnic minority conflict within Southeast Asian countries--all members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN). Utilizing a proposed model (which contextualizes, as of presentation, nine [9] individual case studies of ASEAN member-nations), this study makes the following arguments. First, Southeast Asia\u2019s ethnic, political, and cultural diversity continues to pose major policy and governance hurdles towards enforcing a common community--borne out of the post-colonial nationalist baggage of almost all these countries. Second, each Southeast Asian country's nation-building policies favor a particular/existing ethnic or \u201cethno-religious\u201d majority (chosen specifically by the post-colonial states' bid for accumulating capital to bolster its authority)--at the expense of democratic accountability. Third, ASEAN\u2019s \u201cnon-interference\u201d clause gives leeway to each member state to respond to their ethnic diversity with exclusionary and discriminatory nation-building, as a means of imposing exclusive governance. These setups perpetuate and intensify domestic conflicts and stymies meaningful regional exchange. The study also points to further points of inquiry and research to address this phenomenon.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 55335425, "asset_id": 35472959, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 403456, "first_name": "Hansley", "last_name": "Juliano", "domain_name": "ateneo", "page_name": "HansleyJuliano", "display_name": "Hansley  Juliano", "profile_url": "https://ateneo.academia.edu/HansleyJuliano?f_ri=1948480", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/403456/126465/8287958/s65_hansley.juliano.jpg"}, 