07 up to the present. Based on a review of the structure of the ASEAN and a tally of racial conflicts within five Southeast Asian countries, we offer two observations. First, the situation in Southeast Asia parallels the growth of an anti-regionalist sentiment in Europe due to supposed violations of national sovereignty. Second, and perhaps more importantly, due to the fraught histories and conditions of nation-state consolidation experienced by the ASEAN member countries, they do not\nfit in the scheme of cross-national integration as framed by the ASEAN itself.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 48188358, "asset_id": 27675472, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 403456, "first_name": "Hansley", "last_name": "Juliano", "domain_name": "ateneo", "page_name": "HansleyJuliano", "display_name": "Hansley  Juliano", "profile_url": "https://ateneo.academia.edu/HansleyJuliano?f_ri=1948480", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/403456/126465/8287958/s65_hansley.juliano.jpg"}, {"id": 699262, "first_name": "Matt", "last_name": "Ordo\u00f1ez", "domain_name": "sjtu", "page_name": "MattOrdo\u00f1ez", "display_name": "Matt Ordo\u00f1ez", "profile_url": "https://sjtu.academia.edu/MattOrdo%C3%B1ez?f_ri=1948480", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/699262/2675277/22329071/s65_matt.ordo_ez.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 797, "name": "International Relations", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/International_Relations?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 15466, "name": "Bangsamoro Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Bangsamoro_Studies?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 16211, "name": "Ethnic Conflict", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Ethnic_Conflict?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 27881, "name": "Burma Studies", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Burma_Studies?f_ri=1948480", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 47767, "name": "Singapore Politics", "url": "